Psalm 133

1 How góod and how pléasant it ís,
when bróthers líve in únity!

2 It is like précious óil upon the héad,
running dówn upon the béard,
running dówn upon Áaron’s béard,
upon the cóllar of his róbes;

3 Like the déw of Hérmon, which runs dówn
on the móuntains of Síon.
For thére the LÓRD bestows his bléssing:
life foréver.
